Poem describing one of the floats in the Argonautica by Francesco Cini, a mock naval battle held on the river Arno to celebrate the marriage of Cosimo II de Medici and Maria Maddalena of Austria. This float is named "Castore e Polluce" and belonged to Paulo Giordano and the Principe Peretti. It is depicted in an etching by Matthias Greuter included Camillo Rinuccini's "Descrizione delle feste fatte nelle reali nozze de' serenissimi principi di Toscana."
